PROPOSED SYSTEM
The proposed Smart Helmet Monitoring System is designed to improve worker safety by integrating advanced sensors, a microcontroller, and wireless communication technology into a safety helmet. The system continuously monitors both the health condition of the worker and the surrounding environmental conditions in real time.
The helmet is equipped with various sensors such as temperature sensors, heart rate sensors, oxygen level sensors, and gas sensors to monitor the worker’s vital signs and detect harmful gases in the environment. An accelerometer is also included to detect sudden movements or falls, which may indicate accidents. All the sensors are connected to the ESP32 microcontroller, which acts as the central processing unit of the system.
