5.	Alert and Notification System: If any abnormal condition such as high gas concentration, abnormal heart rate, extreme temperature, or a fall is detected, the system automatically sends alerts to supervisors or emergency responders. Notifications can be sent through mobile alerts, alarms, or cloud-based monitoring systems.
6.	Real-Time Monitoring and Data Logging: All sensor data is continuously logged and monitored in real time. This allows supervisors to track worker health conditions and environmental safety levels, helping them respond quickly to dangerous situations.
Through this methodology, the Smart Helmet Monitoring System ensures continuous monitoring, early hazard detection, and quick emergency response, thereby improving the overall safety of workers in hazardous workplaces.

