6.8 ESP32 – CAM MODULE
	The ESP32-CAM module is an advanced component integrated into the Industrial Safety Smart Helmet Monitoring System to provide real-time visual monitoring and surveillance. In hazardous industrial environments such as construction sites, mines, and chemical plants, visual information plays a critical role in assessing worker safety and surrounding conditions. The ESP32-CAM enhances the system by enabling live video streaming and image capture, allowing supervisors to remotely monitor workers and their environment.
The ESP32-CAM is based on the ESP32 microcontroller with an onboard OV2640 camera module, capable of capturing images and streaming video over Wi-Fi. It supports various resolutions, including JPEG image capture, and can transmit data wirelessly using built-in Wi-Fi connectivity. The module also includes a microSD card slot for local storage of images and videos, making it suitable for both real-time and offline monitoring.
In the smart helmet system, the ESP32-CAM is used as a secondary module dedicated to video processing. It captures real-time visuals from the worker’s perspective and transmits them to a remote monitoring system or mobile application via Wi-Fi. This allows supervisors to observe working conditions, detect hazards visually, and verify the safety of workers without being physically present at the site.
 
The key functions of the ESP32-CAM in this system include:
