6.9 POWER SUPPLY
	The power supply is a crucial part of the Industrial Safety Smart Helmet Monitoring System, as it ensures reliable and continuous operation of all electronic components integrated into the helmet. Since the system is designed as a wearable device, it requires a compact, lightweight, and efficient power source that can support multiple sensors, microcontrollers, and communication modules simultaneously.
In this system, a rechargeable battery (typically 3.7V Li-ion or Li-Po battery) is used as the primary power source. This battery is chosen due to its high energy density, lightweight nature, and long operational life, making it ideal for portable applications like smart helmets. The battery provides a stable DC supply, which is essential for the proper functioning of components such as the ESP32 microcontroller, sensors (DHT11, MQ-8, MPU6050, MAX30102), GPS module, and ESP32-CAM.
To ensure proper voltage levels for different components, a voltage regulation mechanism is used. Since most sensors and modules operate at 3.3V or 5V, voltage regulators (such as AMS1117 or 7805) or DC-DC converters are employed to maintain a constant output voltage. This prevents damage to components caused by voltage fluctuations and ensures stable system performance.
Additionally, proper power management techniques are implemented to optimize battery usage. The ESP32 supports low-power modes such as deep sleep, which can significantly reduce power consumption when the system is idle. This helps in extending battery life and improving overall efficiency.
The power supply design also includes filtering components such as capacitors, which help in reducing noise and ensuring smooth voltage output. This is particularly important in sensor-based systems where accurate readings depend on stable power conditions.
In conclusion, the power supply system is designed to be efficient, reliable, and suitable for wearable applications, ensuring uninterrupted operation of the smart helmet. A well-designed power system not only enhances performance but also plays a key role in maintaining the safety and usability of the device in real-world industrial environments.

